    {
      "id": 15,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "About these counts",
      "datasource": null,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 43
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Hort's architecture **externalises entity counts** \u2014 there is intentionally *no* Prometheus gauge for the live number of repositories or artifacts (the metrics catalog keeps only summary signals). The panels below are honest **Prometheus-derived proxies**: *Artifacts ingested* is the all-time cumulative success counter (not a current inventory), and *Active repositories* counts repositories that have any `hort_ingest_total` series. For an **exact live inventory** (`SELECT count(*) FROM repositories|artifacts`) add a PostgreSQL data source and a table panel \u2014 see `deploy/observability/README.md`."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Artifacts ingested (cumulative, all-time)",
      "description": "Cumulative successful ingests since process start \u2014 NOT a live count.",
